### ─── BASE URL ─────────────────────────────────────────────
@base = http://localhost:4004


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  MASTER DATA SERVICE — Read Tests
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all Suppliers
GET {{base}}/master-data/Suppliers

###

### Get all Categories
GET {{base}}/master-data/Categories

###

### Get all Products
GET {{base}}/master-data/Products

###

### Get one Product by ID
GET {{base}}/master-data/Products/22339209-2694-45c2-91d7-d1aa2b4472c4

###

### Get Products with Supplier expanded
GET {{base}}/master-data/Products?$expand=supplier,category


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  SALES SERVICE — Read Tests
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all Customers
GET {{base}}/sales/Customers

###

### Get all Sales Orders
GET {{base}}/sales/SalesOrders

###

### Get Sales Orders with Customer and Items expanded
GET {{base}}/sales/SalesOrders?$expand=customer,items

###

### Filter Sales Orders by status
GET {{base}}/sales/SalesOrders?$filter=status eq 'New'

###

### Get Sales Order Items
GET {{base}}/sales/SalesOrderItems


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  PROCUREMENT SERVICE — Read Tests
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all Purchase Orders
GET {{base}}/procurement/PurchaseOrders

###

### Get Purchase Orders with Supplier and Items expanded
GET {{base}}/procurement/PurchaseOrders?$expand=supplier,items

###

### Get Stock
GET {{base}}/procurement/Stock


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  SALES SERVICE — CREATE Tests (Handler Validation)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### ✅ Test 1 — Create Sales Order with VALID customer (should succeed)
POST {{base}}/sales/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_ID": "64315681-9895-4132-b929-4d2cd16d0faa",
  "orderDate": "2024-06-01",
  "deliveryDate": "2024-06-15",
  "status": "New",
  "priority": "High",
  "currency_code": "INR"
}

###

### ✅ Test 2 — Create Sales Order Item (auto-calculates price from product)
# Copy the ID returned from Test 1 above and paste below as order_ID
# @name createSalesOrderItem
POST {{base}}/sales/SalesOrderItems
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_ID": "PASTE_ORDER_ID_FROM_TEST1_HERE",
  "product_ID": "22339209-2694-45c2-91d7-d1aa2b4472c4",
  "quantity": 2,
  "deliveryDate": "2024-06-15"
}

###

### ❌ Test 3 — Create Sales Order with FAKE customer (expect 404)
POST {{base}}/sales/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_ID": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "orderDate": "2024-06-01",
  "currency_code": "INR"
}

###

### ❌ Test 4 — Create Sales Order with NO customer (expect 400)
POST {{base}}/sales/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderDate": "2024-06-01",
  "currency_code": "INR"
}

###

### ❌ Test 5 — Create Sales Order Item with EXCESS quantity (expect 409 stock error)
# Laptop Pro 15 has stock = 50, requesting 999
POST {{base}}/sales/SalesOrderItems
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_ID": "PASTE_ORDER_ID_FROM_TEST1_HERE",
  "product_ID": "22339209-2694-45c2-91d7-d1aa2b4472c4",
  "quantity": 999,
  "deliveryDate": "2024-06-15"
}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  PROCUREMENT SERVICE — CREATE Tests (Handler Validation)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### ✅ Test 6 — Create Purchase Order with VALID active supplier (should succeed)
# @name createPurchaseOrder
POST {{base}}/procurement/PurchaseOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "supplier_ID": "16532333-a7ea-40b9-930c-b4189bebc492",
  "orderDate": "2024-06-01",
  "currency_code": "INR",
  "status": "Draft"
}

###

### ❌ Test 7 — Create Purchase Order with FAKE supplier (expect 404)
POST {{base}}/procurement/PurchaseOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "supplier_ID": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "orderDate": "2024-06-01",
  "currency_code": "INR"
}

###

### ❌ Test 8 — Create Purchase Order with NO supplier (expect 400)
POST {{base}}/procurement/PurchaseOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderDate": "2024-06-01",
  "currency_code": "INR"
}